<subSubSection lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[189,1399,980,1293]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[189,491,980,1006]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[297,357,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 38)
</bibRefCitation>
mention two different taxa: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cretzschmar" authorityYear="1826" box="[832,961,980,1006]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clivosus">
<emphasis box="[832,961,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. clivosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Andersen" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1021,1266,980,1006]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="clivosus" subSpecies="zuluensis">
<emphasis box="[1021,1266,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. clivosus zuluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where the latter name is applied to specimens from the (south)western part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1026,1086,1016,1042]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">DRC</collectingCountry>
(Sud-Kivu, Haut-Lomami and Haut-Katanga). However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernard &amp; Happold" box="[548,937,1051,1078]" firstAuthor="Bernard" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="316 - 318" refId="ref257721" refString="Bernard R. T. F. &amp; Happold M. 2013 a. Rhinolophus clivosus Geoffroy's Horseshoe Bat (Cretzschmar's Horseshoe Bat). In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 316 - 318. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="a">Bernard &amp; Happold (2013a: 316)</bibRefCitation>
mention coastal 
<collectingCountry box="[1136,1285,1051,1077]" name="South Africa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">South Africa</collectingCountry>
as region for the 
<taxonomicName box="[281,389,1087,1113]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zuluensis">
<emphasis box="[281,389,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">zuluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subspecies. They do not provide any information on the identity of the subspecies occurring in the 
<collectingCountry box="[386,450,1123,1149]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">DRC</collectingCountry>
. Based on the boundaries set by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernard &amp; Happold" box="[842,1242,1123,1150]" firstAuthor="Bernard" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="316 - 318" refId="ref257721" refString="Bernard R. T. F. &amp; Happold M. 2013 a. Rhinolophus clivosus Geoffroy's Horseshoe Bat (Cretzschmar's Horseshoe Bat). In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 316 - 318. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="a">Bernard &amp; Happold (2013a: 316)</bibRefCitation>
, the northern specimens (from Nord- and Sud-Kivu and from 
<collectingCountry box="[770,866,1158,1184]" name="Rwanda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[927,1025,1158,1185]" name="Burundi" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Burundi</collectingCountry>
) might possibly be assigned to 
<emphasis box="[189,297,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">keniensis</emphasis>
Hollister, 1916, and those from Haut-Lomami and Haut-Katanga to 
<emphasis box="[1096,1166,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">augur</emphasis>
K. Andersen, 1904. The subspecific assignment of the westernmost specimen (RMCA 7718 from Kisantu, Kongo Central Province) cannot be performed as no other specimens from that area are known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[189,1398,1332,1430]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
The Rwandan locality here attributed to 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[668,921,1332,1359]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[775,834,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(1966)
</bibRefCitation>
refers to three specimens from Bugoye- Kisenyi, Western Prefecture (RMCA 12265 to 12267), which were originally assigned to 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1842" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fumigatus">Rhinolophus fumigatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[189,1399,1469,1532]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Recent research on nuclear introns by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dool" box="[613,867,1469,1496]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Dool" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="196 - 212" refId="ref259689" refString="Dool S. E., Puechmaille S. J., Foley N. M., Allegrini B., Bastian A., Mutumi G. L., Maluleke T. G., Odendaal L. J., Teeling E. C. &amp; Jacobs D. S. 2016. Nuclear introns outperform mitochondrial DNA in inter-specific phylogenetic reconstruction: Lessons from horseshoe bats (Rhinolophidae: Chiroptera). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 97: 196 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2016.01.003" type="journal article" year="2016">
Dool 
<emphasis box="[676,731,1470,1496]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2016: 202)
</bibRefCitation>
indicates that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cretzschmar" authorityYear="1826" box="[1026,1147,1470,1496]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clivosus">
<emphasis box="[1026,1147,1470,1496]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. clivosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is paraphyletic, which would suggest that some of the currently recognized subspecies might represent valid, separate species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[189,1399,1571,2028]" lastBlockId="37.[189,1399,267,404]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<bibRefCitation author="Stoffberg" box="[189,450,1571,1597]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Stoffberg" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="31946" refId="ref273541" refString="Stoffberg S., Schoeman M. C. &amp; Matthee C. A. 2012. Correlated genetic and ecological diversification in a widespread southern African horseshoe bat. PLoS One 7 (2) e 31946. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0031946" type="journal article" year="2012">
Stoffberg 
<emphasis box="[306,365,1571,1597]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
already found that the mtDNA control region of the southern African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cretzschmar" authorityYear="1826" box="[1271,1399,1571,1597]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clivosus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1399,1571,1597]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. clivosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens differed considerably from that of northern populations (as much as they differ from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[189,401,1643,1669]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferrumequinum">
<emphasis box="[189,401,1643,1669]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. ferrumequinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). They suggest to call these 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1829" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1829" box="[723,1009,1643,1669]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[723,859,1643,1669]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. geoffroyi</emphasis>
Smith, 1829
</taxonomicName>
. However, they also point out that it “… is not currently recognized as a separate species because the name was unidentifiable and the 
<typeStatus box="[1330,1381,1679,1705]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
specimen apparently lost …” This was already mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellerman" box="[902,1205,1714,1741]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Ellerman" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref259932" refString="Ellerman J. R., Morrison-Scott T. C. S. &amp; Hayman R. W. 1953. Southern African Mammals 1758 to 1951: a Reclassification. Trustees of the British Museum (Natural History), London. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 113025" type="book" year="1953">
Ellerman 
<emphasis box="[1016,1074,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(1953: 56)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="277 - 295" refId="ref265677" refString="Hayman R. W. 1954. Notes on some African bats, mainly from the Belgian Congo. Revue de zoologie et de botanique africaines 50 (3 - 4): 277 - 295." type="journal article" year="1954">Hayman (1954: 284)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Csorba" box="[307,545,1750,1776]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Csorba" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref259311" refString="Csorba G., Ujhelyi P. &amp; Thomas N. 2003. Horseshoe Bats of the World (Chiroptera: Rhinolophidae). Alana Books, Shropshire, UK." type="book" year="2003">
Csorba 
<emphasis box="[397,455,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stoffberg" box="[556,817,1750,1776]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Stoffberg" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="31946" refId="ref273541" refString="Stoffberg S., Schoeman M. C. &amp; Matthee C. A. 2012. Correlated genetic and ecological diversification in a widespread southern African horseshoe bat. PLoS One 7 (2) e 31946. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0031946" type="journal article" year="2012">
Stoffberg 
<emphasis box="[673,731,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
do not provide any information that substantiates the validity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1829" box="[370,475,1786,1812]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[370,475,1786,1812]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so we are reluctant to use this name. They also indicate that “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1829" box="[1245,1386,1786,1812]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[1245,1386,1786,1812]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” includes four subspecies: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1829" box="[489,594,1822,1848]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[489,594,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in western 
<collectingCountry box="[727,787,1822,1848]" name="South Africa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">RSA</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[798,906,1822,1848]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zuluensis">
<emphasis box="[798,906,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">zuluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1031,1091,1822,1848]" name="South Africa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">RSA</collectingCountry>
, 
<emphasis box="[1102,1172,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">augur</emphasis>
in central 
<collectingCountry box="[1294,1351,1822,1848]" name="South Africa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">RSA</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[189,305,1858,1884]" name="Botswana" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Botswana</collectingCountry>
and 
<emphasis box="[363,516,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">zambesiensis</emphasis>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[554,712,1857,1883]" name="Mozambique" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[724,853,1857,1883]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[865,955,1857,1883]" name="Zambia" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and the southeastern-most part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[189,249,1893,1919]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">DRC</collectingCountry>
(Sakania Territory, Haut-Katanga Province). The latter area is just southeast of the records from Haut-Katanga we report here, and seems to suggest that they do not belong to “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1829" box="[1123,1261,1929,1955]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geoffroyi">
<emphasis box="[1123,1261,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. geoffroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stoffberg" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Stoffberg" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="31946" refId="ref273541" refString="Stoffberg S., Schoeman M. C. &amp; Matthee C. A. 2012. Correlated genetic and ecological diversification in a widespread southern African horseshoe bat. PLoS One 7 (2) e 31946. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0031946" type="journal article" year="2012">
Stoffberg 
<emphasis box="[189,250,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2012: 6)
</bibRefCitation>
considered specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[713,790,1965,1991]" name="Kenya" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Kenya</collectingCountry>
to belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cretzschmar" authorityYear="1826" box="[952,1081,1965,1991]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clivosus">
<emphasis box="[952,1081,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">R. clivosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which might suggest that the more northern CRB specimens (Sud- and Nord-Kivu, 
<collectingCountry box="[882,978,2001,2027]" name="Burundi" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Burundi</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1039,1137,2001,2028]" name="Rwanda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
) could be assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cretzschmar" authorityYear="1826" box="[189,316,267,293]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clivosus">
<emphasis box="[189,316,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. clivosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. On the other hand, 
<bibRefCitation author="Benda &amp; Vallo" box="[561,868,267,293]" firstAuthor="Benda" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="69 - 96" refId="ref256872" refString="Benda P. &amp; Vallo P. 2012. New look on the geographical variation in Rhinolophus clivosus with description of a new horseshoe bat species from Cyrenaica, Libya. Vespertilio 16: 69 - 96. Available from http: // www. ceson. org / vespertilio / 16 / 069 _ 096 _ Benda. pdf [accessed 29 Nov. 2017]." type="journal article" year="2012">Benda &amp; Vallo (2012: 83)</bibRefCitation>
indicate that all populations occurring in the savanna belt from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[560,617,304,330]" name="South Africa" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">RSA</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[652,729,305,331]" name="Kenya" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Kenya</collectingCountry>
belong to one taxon, for which 
<emphasis box="[1102,1172,305,330]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">augur</emphasis>
K. Andersen, 1904 is the prior available name. However, pending further research into the systematics of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cretzschmar" authorityYear="1826" box="[1269,1399,341,367]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clivosus">
<emphasis box="[1269,1399,341,367]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. clivosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, we tentatively retain the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cretzschmar" authorityYear="1826" box="[665,793,378,404]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clivosus">
<emphasis box="[665,793,378,404]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">R. clivosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for all the CRB specimens.
</paragraph>
